<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>RH124 Exam — Task Sheet</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: monospace; max-width: 860px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 0 20px; background: #f5f5f5; color: #222; }
  #landing { text-align: center; margin-top: 120px; }
  #landing h1 { font-size: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  #landing p { color: #555; margin-bottom: 24px; }
  #num-input { font-size: 1.4em; width: 80px; text-align: center; padding: 8px; border: 2px solid #aaa; border-radius: 4px; }
  #go-btn { font-size: 1.2em; padding: 9px 24px; margin-left: 12px; background: #c00; color: #fff; border: none; border-radius: 4px; cursor: pointer; }
  #go-btn:hover { background: #a00; }
  #sheet { display: none; }
  .header { border-bottom: 2px solid #c00; padding-bottom: 12px; margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .header h1 { margin: 0 0 4px 0; font-size: 1.3em; }
  .header .meta { color: #555; font-size: 0.9em; }
  .task { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 4px; padding: 20px 24px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .task-header { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; padding-bottom: 8px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .task-title { font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.05em; }
  .task-meta { color: #777; font-size: 0.85em; }
  .task ol { margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; }
  .task li { margin-bottom: 8px; line-height: 1.5; }
  .pts { color: #c00; font-weight: bold; font-size: 0.85em; }
  .note { background: #fffbe6; border-left: 3px solid #e6a817; padding: 8px 12px; margin: 12px 0; font-size: 0.9em; }
  .hint-box { background: #f0f4ff; border-left: 3px solid #4466cc; padding: 8px 12px; margin-top: 14px; font-size: 0.88em; color: #334; }
  .hint-box strong { display: block; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  code { background: #eee; padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.95em; }
  .tip { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-top: 8px; }
  .footer { text-align: center; margin-top: 32px; padding: 16px; color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; border-top: 1px solid #ddd; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div id="landing">
  <h1>RH124 Mid-Semester Practical Exam</h1>
  <p>Virovitica University of Applied Sciences &mdash; Enter your student number to load your task sheet.</p>
  <input id="num-input" type="number" min="1" max="20" placeholder="1–20" autofocus>
  <button id="go-btn" onclick="loadSheet()">Load</button>
  <p id="err-msg" style="color:#c00;display:none;">Invalid number. Enter a value between 1 and 20.</p>
</div>

<div id="sheet"></div>

<script>
const variants = [
{% for host in groups['students'] | sort %}
{% set h = hostvars[host] %}
  {
    num: {{ loop.index }},
    host: "{{ host }}",
    variant: "{{ h.exam_variant }}",
    dir: "{{ h.exam_dir }}",
    username: "{{ h.exam_username }}",
    gid: "{{ h.exam_gid }}",
    expiry: "{{ h.exam_expiry }}",
    workspace: "{{ h.exam_workspace }}",
    mount: "{{ h.exam_mount }}",
    mount_text: "{{ h.exam_mount_text }}",
    extra_package: "{{ h.exam_extra_package }}"
  }{{ "," if not loop.last }}
{% endfor %}
];

function loadSheet() {
  const val = parseInt(document.getElementById('num-input').value);
  if (isNaN(val) || val < 1 || val > 20) {
    document.getElementById('err-msg').style.display = 'block';
    return;
  }
  document.getElementById('err-msg').style.display = 'none';
  const v = variants[val - 1];
  document.getElementById('landing').style.display = 'none';
  document.getElementById('sheet').style.display = 'block';
  document.getElementById('sheet').innerHTML = renderSheet(v);
}

document.getElementById('num-input').addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
  if (e.key === 'Enter') loadSheet();
});

function renderSheet(v) {
  return `
<div class="header">
  <h1>RH124 Mid-Semester Practical Exam</h1>
  <div class="meta">Student: <strong>${v.host}</strong> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Variant: <strong>${v.variant}</strong> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Duration: 90 min &nbsp;|&nbsp; Total: 100 pts</div>
</div>

<div class="task">
  <div class="task-header">
    <span class="task-title">Task 1 &mdash; File and Directory Management</span>
    <span class="task-meta">15 pts &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; ~12 min &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; Easy</span>
  </div>
  <p>You are organizing project files for the university IT department.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Create the directory <code>/home/student/projects/${v.dir}</code> with all intermediate directories. <span class="pts">(2 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Inside that directory, create three empty files: <code>report.txt</code>, <code>backup.txt</code>, <code>notes.txt</code>. <span class="pts">(2 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Copy <code>/etc/hostname</code> to <code>/home/student/projects/${v.dir}/hostname.txt</code>. <span class="pts">(2 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Append the last 5 lines of <code>/etc/passwd</code> to <code>/home/student/projects/${v.dir}/report.txt</code>. <span class="pts">(3 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Create a hard link to <code>report.txt</code> at the path <code>/home/student/projects/report-link-${v.variant}</code>. <span class="pts">(3 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Create a symbolic link to <code>/home/student/projects/${v.dir}</code> at the path <code>/home/student/exam-shortcut</code>. <span class="pts">(3 pts)</span></li>
  </ol>
  <div class="hint-box"><strong>Hint</strong>Use <code>mkdir</code> with a flag that creates all missing intermediate directories at once. Hard links and symbolic links are both created with <code>ln</code> — check the man page for the relevant options.</div>
</div>

<div class="task">
  <div class="task-header">
    <span class="task-title">Task 2 &mdash; User, Group, and Password Policy</span>
    <span class="task-meta">20 pts &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; ~15 min &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; Easy-Medium</span>
  </div>
  <p>You are provisioning accounts for a new team of database administrators.</p>
  <div class="note">The <code>dbteam</code> group already exists on your system &mdash; do not delete and recreate it, just confirm the GID matches and proceed.</div>
  <ol>
    <li>Create a group named <code>dbteam</code> with GID <code>${v.gid}</code>. <span class="pts">(3 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Create a user named <code>${v.username}</code> with:
      <ul>
        <li><code>dbteam</code> as a supplementary group <span class="pts">(2 pts)</span></li>
        <li>Initial password: <code>Welcome1</code> <span class="pts">(2 pts)</span></li>
        <li>Password must be changed on first login <span class="pts">(3 pts)</span></li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Set the following password policy for <code>${v.username}</code>: <span class="pts">(6 pts &mdash; 2 each)</span>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum days between password changes: <code>7</code></li>
        <li>Maximum days before password change required: <code>60</code></li>
        <li>Account expiry date: <code>${v.expiry}</code></li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Allow <code>${v.username}</code> to run any command with <code>sudo</code> without a password prompt. Use a dedicated file in <code>/etc/sudoers.d/</code>. <span class="pts">(4 pts)</span></li>
  </ol>
  <div class="hint-box"><strong>Hint</strong>Use <code>chage</code> to configure password aging and expiry. For <code>sudo</code> without a password, check the syntax of existing files in <code>/etc/sudoers.d/</code>.</div>
</div>

<div class="task">
  <div class="task-header">
    <span class="task-title">Task 3 &mdash; File Permissions and Collaborative Directory</span>
    <span class="task-meta">20 pts &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; ~15 min &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; Medium</span>
  </div>
  <p>The <code>dbteam</code> group needs a shared workspace where all members can create and modify files, but cannot delete each other's work.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Create the directory <code>/home/${v.workspace}</code>. <span class="pts">(2 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Set the group owner of the directory to <code>dbteam</code>. <span class="pts">(3 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Set permissions so that the owner has full rwx, group members have rwx, and all other users have no access. <span class="pts">(5 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Set the <strong>SGID bit</strong> on the directory so that new files automatically inherit the <code>dbteam</code> group. <span class="pts">(4 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Set the <strong>sticky bit</strong> on the directory so that users can only delete their own files. <span class="pts">(4 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Configure <code>${v.username}</code>'s shell so that <code>umask</code> is persistently set to <code>007</code>. <span class="pts">(2 pts)</span></li>
  </ol>
  <p class="tip">Expected final permissions on the directory: <code>drwxrws--T</code></p>
  <div class="hint-box"><strong>Hint</strong>Special bits (SGID, sticky) can be set with <code>chmod</code> using letters (<code>s</code>, <code>t</code>) or as an octal prefix. To make <code>umask</code> persistent, add it to the user's shell startup file that runs for every interactive shell.</div>
</div>

<div class="task">
  <div class="task-header">
    <span class="task-title">Task 4 &mdash; Service Management</span>
    <span class="task-meta">15 pts &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; ~10 min &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; Easy</span>
  </div>
  <div class="note"><strong>Important:</strong> Changes must survive a reboot. Reboot your VM before running final grading: <code>sudo systemctl reboot</code></div>
  <ol>
    <li>Ensure the <code>crond</code> service is <strong>running</strong> and <strong>enabled</strong> to start automatically on boot. <span class="pts">(5 pts)</span></li>
    <li><strong>Stop</strong> the <code>rsyslog</code> service and <strong>disable</strong> it so it does not start on boot. <span class="pts">(5 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Reboot the system and verify both services are in the correct state after boot. <span class="pts">(5 pts)</span></li>
  </ol>
  <div class="hint-box"><strong>Hint</strong>Use <code>systemctl</code> to start, stop, enable, and disable services. Verify with <code>systemctl is-active</code> and <code>systemctl is-enabled</code>.</div>
</div>

<div class="task">
  <div class="task-header">
    <span class="task-title">Task 5 &mdash; Package Management and Custom Repository</span>
    <span class="task-meta">15 pts &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; ~12 min &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; Medium</span>
  </div>
  <ol>
    <li>Create a DNF repository configuration file at <code>/etc/yum.repos.d/exam.repo</code> with: <span class="pts">(6 pts)</span>
      <ul>
        <li>Repository name: <code>Exam Repository</code></li>
        <li>Base URL: <code>http://172.16.16.121/repo</code></li>
        <li>Enabled: yes</li>
        <li>GPG check: disabled</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Install the package <code>vim-enhanced</code>. <span class="pts">(3 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Install the package <code>${v.extra_package}</code>. <span class="pts">(3 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Ensure the package <code>tmux</code> is <strong>not installed</strong> &mdash; remove it if present. <span class="pts">(3 pts)</span></li>
  </ol>
  <div class="hint-box"><strong>Hint</strong>Look at an existing <code>.repo</code> file in <code>/etc/yum.repos.d/</code> for the correct format. Use <code>dnf remove</code> to uninstall and <code>rpm -q</code> to verify.</div>
</div>

<div class="task">
  <div class="task-header">
    <span class="task-title">Task 6 &mdash; Mount a File System and Search for Files</span>
    <span class="task-meta">15 pts &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; ~15 min &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; Medium-Hard</span>
  </div>
  <p>A new disk has been attached to your system. It is available as <code>/dev/sdb</code> with one partition <code>/dev/sdb1</code> (already formatted as XFS).</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Create a mount point at <code>${v.mount}</code>. <span class="pts">(2 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Mount <code>/dev/sdb1</code> persistently by adding an entry to <code>/etc/fstab</code>. Use the <strong>UUID</strong> (recommended) or the device path. The mount must survive a reboot. <span class="pts">(5 pts)</span></li>
    <li>After mounting, create a file at <code>${v.mount}/mounted.txt</code> containing exactly the text: <code>${v.mount_text}</code> <span class="pts">(2 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Find all files in <code>/etc</code> that are <strong>larger than 50 KB</strong> and save the full path list to <code>${v.mount}/large-files.txt</code>. <span class="pts">(3 pts)</span></li>
    <li>Find all files in <code>/var</code> owned by user <code>root</code> and group <code>root</code> with permissions <strong>exactly <code>640</code></strong>, and save the full path list to <code>${v.mount}/perms-files.txt</code>. <span class="pts">(3 pts)</span></li>
  </ol>
  <div class="hint-box"><strong>Hint</strong>Use <code>lsblk -fp</code> to find the UUID of a block device. Suppress errors in <code>find</code> output with <code>2&gt;/dev/null</code>. Persistent mounts go in <code>/etc/fstab</code> and are read at boot time.</div>
</div>

<div class="footer">
  Run <code>grade</code> to check all tasks &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; Run <code>grade t3</code> to check a specific task &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; Run <code>hint t3</code> for guidance
</div>
`;
}
</script>
</body>
</html>
